  "body": "**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Bug Report\r\n\r\n**Bug Report**\r\n\r\nAfter using a Rook-provisioned NFS server for a while, we have observed the memory usage growing very large - over 4GB in one case.\r\n\r\nThis is not the nfs-ganesha server itself, but the `rook` binary in the same container.\r\n\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (minimal and precise):**\r\n\r\n1. Deploy nfs operator and an NFSServer.\r\n2. Create a workload with persistent storage using the NFS server.\r\n3. Write a bunch of files into the share\r\n\r\ne.g in workload container: \r\n```\r\ncd /mounted/nfs/path\r\nfor i in {1..1000}; do dd if=/dev/zero of=test$i bs=20k count=1; done\r\n```\r\n\r\nRunning `top` in the NFS server container at the same time, observe the RESident memory of the `rook` process increases - around 35MB each time here.\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n* rook: v1.1.4\r\n* Linux 4.19.0-0.bpo.6-amd64 #1 SMP Debian 4.19.67-2+deb10u1~bpo9+1 (2019-09-30) x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux\r\n* DigitalOcean Kubernetes Service\r\n",
